Margaret Milner Richardson J.D.: Executive Profile & Biography - Bloomberg









































  





















































































July 21, 2017 2:08 PM ET
Diversified Consumer Services

Company Overview of Jackson Hewitt Tax Service Inc.



SnapshotPeople 




OverviewBoard MembersCommittees



Executive Profile
Margaret Milner Richardson J.D.Non-Executive Chairman, Jackson Hewitt Tax Service Inc.AgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 2 Board Members in 2 different organizations across 2 different industries.See Board Relationships74--
Background

		Ms. Margaret Milner Richardson, also known as Peggy, has been a Director of Legg Mason, Inc. since November 6, 2003. Ms. Richardson also serves on the Boards of the Eurasia Foundation and the Eurasia Partnership Foundation, the Protestant Episcopal Cathedral Foundation, Taxpayers Against Fraud, the Piedmont Environmental Council, Virginians for Sensible Energy Policies and the National Museum of Women in the Arts. Previously, she spent several years as a Tax Partner ... at Ernst & Young, where she served as the National Director of IRS Practice and Procedure. Prior to that, she headed the Internal Revenue Service from 1993 until 1997 as Commissioner and served on the Internal Revenue Service Commissioner's Advisory Group from 1988 to 1990 and chaired the group in 1990. As Commissioner, she worked on tax administration and taxpayer service, while also working with tax administrators in foreign jurisdictions. Previously, Ms. Richardson worked at a private firm in Washington. Prior to that, she clerked at the U.S. Court of Claims and then joined the Office of Chief Counsel of the Internal Revenue Service. Previously, she served as a Director of Jackson Hewitt Tax Service Inc. from June 2004 through August 2011. She also served on the Boards of several nonprofit organizations, including USA for UNHCR, which she chaired; the Women's Campaign Fund; The Fishing School; and the National Cathedral School for Girls, where she served as President of the Parents' Association. Ms. Richardson is a member of the District of Columbia and Virginia bars, a Fellow of the American Bar Foundation and on the ALI-ABA Advisory Panel on Business and Corporate Law. She is also a member of the Washington Women's Forum and the International Women's Forum. Ms. Richardson was named Woman of the Year by the Financial Women's Association and she is the recipient of the Federal Bar Association Section of Taxation's Kenneth Liles Distinguished Service Award, the Tax Executives Institute Distinguished Service Award and the Hartford Institute Award. She was named a "Washington Woman of Genius" by Trinity College. Ms. Richardson graduated from Vassar College with a degree in Political Science and received her J.D. with honors from The George Washington University Law School.Read Full Background




